Class RunTrackMateOnRecording

    RunTrackMateOnExperiment

    public class RunTrackMateOnRecording
extends TrackMateHeadless
    Provides functionality to run TrackMate analysis for a single microscopy recording. Handles setup, detection, tracking, visualization, and export.

    This class is typically invoked by RunTrackMateOnExperiment as part of batch processing within a Paint project.

      • runTrackMateOnRecording

        public static TrackMateResults runTrackMateOnRecording(Path experimentPath,
                                                       Path imagesPath,
                                                       TrackMateConfig trackMateConfig,
                                                       double threshold,
                                                       ExperimentInfo experimentInfoRecord,
                                                       ProjectDialog dialog)
        Executes the TrackMate pipeline on a given recording. Loads the ND2 image, applies analysis parameters, and writes results.
        Parameters:
        experimentPath - directory where results will be written
        imagesPath - directory containing the ND2 image
        trackMateConfig - configuration object with TrackMate parameters
        threshold - threshold for spot detection
        experimentInfoRecord - metadata describing this recording
        dialog - optional dialog for user cancellation
        Returns:
        TrackMateResults containing analysis statistics, or a cancellation result if aborted
